SIMPLE: puzzle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: puzzle
<hw>puz"zle</hw> <pr>(p⟦ucr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>opposal</ets>, in the sense of problem. See <er>Oppose</er>,
<er>Pose</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something which
perplexes or embarrasses; especially, a toy or a problem contrived for
testing ingenuity; also, something exhibiting marvelous skill in
making.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being puzzled; perplexity; <as>as, to
be in a <ex>puzzle</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>puzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: puzzle
<hw>puz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>puzzled</conjf> <pr>(p⟦ucr⟧z"z'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>puzzling</conjf> <pr>(p⟦ucr⟧z"zl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To perplex; to confuse; to embarrass; to put to a
stand; to nonplus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A very shrewd disputant in those points is dexterous in
<qex>puzzling</qex> others.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is perpetually <qex>puzzled</qex> and perplexed amidst his own
blunders.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make intricate; to entangle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They disentangle from the <qex>puzzled</qex> skein.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ways of Heaven are dark and intricate,⟦br⟧
<qex>Puzzled</qex> in mazes, and perplexed with error.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To solve by ingenuity, as a puzzle; -- followed by
<xex>out</xex>; <as>as, to <ex>puzzle</ex> out a mystery</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To embarrass; perplex; confuse; bewilder;
confound. See <er>Embarrass</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Puzzle
<hw>Puz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To be bewildered, or
perplexed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>puzzling</qex> fool, that heeds nothing.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To work, as at a puzzle; <as>as, to <ex>puzzle</ex>
over a problem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puzzledom</ent>⟦br⟧
